The paper deals with content-based image retrieval (CBIR) using texture and color features, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper involves the use of local descriptors and geometric distance, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves the use of riemannian distances, which is a topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and geometry (cs.GR).
